## Using `DefaultRecordMapper`

Just use a custom `RecordMapper` via [`ResultQuery.fetch(RecordMapper)`][1] and call [`apply`][2] on a mapped value

```kotlin
.fetch {
    it.into(MytargetClass::class.java).apply { 
        static_value = Enum.MY_VALUE
    }
}
```

## Using any other `RecordMapper`

The above just assumes you want to continue using the `DefaultRecordMapper`, which is reflection based. But you don&#39;t have to. You can do anything you want with `it`:

```kotlin
.fetch {
    MytargetClass(it[t.property], Enum.MY_VALUE)
}
```

